From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: bot <bot@example.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 08:40:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix utime usage for MSVC

The utime block in close_and_restore was guarded on the presence of the
utime.h/sys/utime.h headers while the corresponding include at the top
of the file is guarded on HAVE_UTIME, so the struct utimbuf usage did
not compile when the header exists but the function does not. Align the
gates, and map utime/utimbuf to the ISO C names _utime/_utimbuf for the
UCRT, which hides the POSIX names from conforming compilers
(__STDC__ == 1, which clang defines).
---
 src/magic.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/magic.c b/src/magic.c
index 779f024..dbb0262 100644
--- a/src/magic.c
+++ b/src/magic.c
@@ -56,6 +56,12 @@ FILE_RCSID("@(#)$File: magic.c,v 1.125 2026/01/19 18:53:58 christos Exp $")
 # elif defined(HAVE_UTIME_H)
 #  include <utime.h>
 # endif
+# if defined(_MSC_VER)
+   /* The UCRT only exposes the POSIX names when !__STDC__; clang is a
+      conforming compiler, so use the ISO C names. */
+#  define utime _utime
+#  define utimbuf _utimbuf
+# endif
 #endif
 
 #ifdef HAVE_UNISTD_H
@@ -386,7 +392,7 @@ close_and_restore(const struct magic_set *ms, const char *name, int fd,
 	utsbuf[1].tv_sec = sb->st_mtime;
 
 	(void) utimes(name, utsbuf); /* don't care if loses */
-#elif defined(HAVE_UTIME_H) || defined(HAVE_SYS_UTIME_H)
+#elif defined(HAVE_UTIME)
 	struct utimbuf  utbuf;
 
 	(void)memset(&utbuf, 0, sizeof(utbuf));
